&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ST3+ Doctor - Acute frailty - Eastbourne General Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East Sussex Healthcare NHS Trust has invested in an Acute Frailty team at each district hospital site. This investment will allow us to deliver expert care to frail older patients as soon as they arrive in hospital. As part of this investment we are now looking to appoint an ST3 Doctor to join our Care of the Elderly department and the enthusiastic and forward-looking Medical team at Eastbourne General Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are good multidisciplinary links. The Department of Care of the Elderly is dedicated to providing a seamless service to Older People and is working towards the achievement of goals and recommendations in the NSF for Older People. The post is a ST3+ post in Geriatrics and will be part of a team of Consultant, Advanced Specialists and therapists to deliver acute frailty within the hospitals gateways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also be expected to effectively communicate with patients and relatives and respond to any queries or complaints where applicable. The Candidates must hold full GMC with a licence to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Rannie Nahas - Consultant Care Of The Elderly, Eastbourne 0300 131 4500&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rannienahas@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Henry Alexander - Consultant Care of the Elderly, Eastbourne 0300 131 4500&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;henry.alexander2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
